The '''1963 [[Syracuse Orange football|Syracuse Orangemen football]] team''' represented [[Syracuse University]] in the 1963 NCAA University Division college football season. The offense scored 255 points while the defense allowed 101 points. Led by head coach Ben Schwartzwalder, the team won eight games. Despite their 8-2 record, the team did not qualify for a Bowl game.
==Regular season== * Syracuse played in the final college football game played at Yankee Stadium on [[Thanksgiving (United States)|Thanksgiving Day]]. The eighth and final game was played in 1963, with the Orangemen defeating Notre Dame, 14&ndash;7. This was a rematch following the teams' controversial [[1961 Syracuse Orangemen football team|1961]] game won by Notre Dame, 17&ndash;15.
